\par }{\b\fs20 Hit Dice:}{\fs20  The term \'93Hit Dice\'94 is used synonymously with \'93character levels\'94 for effects that affect a number of Hit Dice of creatures.
 A creature with only Hit Dice from its species, not from any classes it may have, has a character level equal to its Hit Dice. A creature with class levels is considered to have Hit Dice equal to the total of its Hit Dice and its class levels.
\par }{\b\fs20 Caster Level:}{\fs20  A spell\rquote s power often depends on caster level, which is the caster\rquote 
s level in the appropriate spellcasting class. Creatures with no classes have a caster level equal to their Hit Dice unless otherwise specified.
\par }{\b\fs20 Creatures and Characters: }{\fs20 \'93Creatures\'94 and \'93characters\'94 are used synonymously in the spell descriptions.
\par }{\b\fs20 List Format:}{\fs20  Spells in the following lists are presented in order of spell level (from lowest to highest) and alphabetized within each level group. A brief description of the spell\rquote s effect is provided.
