\par The caster creates an invisible magical sensor that sends him or her visual information. The caster can create the }{\cs27\fs20 arcane eye}{\fs20  at any point he or she can see, but it can then travel outside the caster\rquote 
s line of sight without hindrance. The }{\cs27\fs20 arcane eye}{\fs20  travels 30 feet per round (300 feet per minute) if viewing an area ahead primarily looking at the floor or 10 feet per
 round (100 feet per minute) if examining the ceiling and walls as well as the floor ahead. The }{\cs27\fs20 arcane eye}{\fs20  sees exactly as the caster would see if he or she were there. The }{\cs27\fs20 arcane eye}{\fs20 
 can travel in any direction as long as the spell lasts. Solid barriers prevent the passage of an }{\cs27\fs20 arcane eye}{\fs20 , although it can pass through a space no smaller than 1 inch in diameter.
\par The caster must concentrate to use the eye. If the caster does not concentrate, the eye is inert until the caster again concentrates.
