 can reverse even an instantaneous effect. For each such effect, the caster makes a check of 
1d20 + caster level (maximum +10) against a DC of 11 + caster level of the effect. Success means that the creature is free of the spell, curse, or effect. For cursed magic items, the DC is 25.
