s center. The energy blast deals 1d4 points of damage (of the given energy type) +1 point per caster level. The item protected by the trap is not harmed by this explosion.
\par The warded item cannot have a second closure or warding spell placed on it.
\par An unsuccessful }{\cs27\fs20 dispel magic}{\fs20  spell does not detonate the spell.
\par Underwater, the acid and fire versions of this spell deal half damage.
\par The caster can use the trapped object without discharging it, as can any individual to whom the spell was specifically attuned when cast. \'93Attuning\'94 to an individual usually involves denoting a password that the caster can share with friends.
\par A successful Search check (DC 29) finds an }{\cs27\fs20 energy trap}{\fs20 , and a successful Disable Device check (DC 29) safely removes it. 
