\par This spell enables the caster or the creature touched to move and attack normally for the duration of the spell, even under the influence of magic that usually impedes movement.
\par The spell also allows a character to move and attack normally while underwater, even with slashing and bludgeoning weapons, provided that the weapon is wielded in the hand rather than hurled. The }{\cs27\fs20 freedom of movement }{\fs20 
spell does not, however, allow water breathing.
