\par This inscription harms those who enter, pass, or open the warded area or object.  
\par The caster sets the conditions of th
e ward. Typically, any creature entering the warded area or opening the warded object without speaking a pass phrase (which the caster sets when casting the spell) is subject to the magic it stores. Alternatively or in addition to a pass phrase trigger, }
{\cs27\fs20 glyphs of warding}{\fs20  can be set according to physical characteristics or creature type, or species. }{\cs27\fs20 Glyphs}{\fs20  can also be set with respect to allegiance. They cannot be set according to class, Hit Dice, or level. }{
\cs27\fs20 Glyphs}{\fs20  respond to invisible creatures normally. Multiple }{\cs27\fs20 glyphs}{\fs20  cannot be cast on the same area. However, they can ward separate compartments of the same object.
\par The }{\cs27\fs20 glyph}{\fs20  can be placed to conform to any shape up to the limitations of the spell\rquote s total square footage. When the spell is completed, the }{\cs27\fs20 glyph}{\fs20  becomes nearly invisible.
\par }{\cs27\fs20 Glyphs}{\fs20  cannot be affected or bypassed by such means as physical or magical probing, though they can be dispelled. Nonmagical disguises cannot fool a }{\cs27\fs20 glyph of warding}{\fs20 .
\par }{\cs27\fs20 Read magic}{\fs20  allows a character to identify a }{\cs27\fs20 glyph of warding}{\fs20  with a successful Spellcraft check (DC 13). Identifying the }{\cs27\fs20 glyph}{\fs20 
 does not discharge it and allows the character to know the basic nature of the }{\cs27\fs20 glyph}{\fs20  (version, type of damage caused, what spell is stored).
\par Detecting the }{\cs27\fs20 glyph}{\fs20  requires a successful Search check (DC 28), and safely removing it requires a successful Disable Device check (DC 28).
\par Depending on the version selected, a }{\cs27\fs20 glyph}{\fs20  either blasts the intruder or activates a spell.
\par }{\b\fs20 Blast Glyph:}{\fs20  A blast deals 1d8 points of damage per two caster levels to the intruder and to all within 5 feet of the intruder (maximum 5d8). This damage is acid, cold, fire, electricity, or sonic/concussion (caster\rquote 
s choice, made at time of casting). Those affected can make Reflex saves to take half damage.
\par }{\b\fs20 Spell Glyph: }{\fs20 The caster can store any harmful spell of up to 3rd level that he or she knows. All level-dependent features of the spell are based on the caster\rquote 
s level at the time of casting. If the spell has targets, it targets the intruder. If the spell normally affects an area, the area or effect is centered on the intruder. All saving throws operate as normal, except that the DC is based on the level of the 
}{\cs27\fs20 glyph}{\fs20 .
\par }{\cs27\b\fs20 Material Component:}{\fs20   Purchase DC 15.
