\par An immobile, faintly shim\-mering magical sphere surrounds the caster and excludes all spell effects of 3rd level and lower. The area or effect of any such spells does not include the area of the }{\cs27\fs20 minor globe of invulnerability}{\fs20 
. Such spells fail to affect any target located wi
thin the globe. This includes spell-like abilities and spells or spell-like effects from objects. However, any type of spell can be cast through or out of the magical globe. Spells of 4th level and higher are not affected by the globe. The globe can be br
ought down by a targeted }{\cs27\fs20 dispel magic }{\fs20 spell, but not by an area }{\cs27\fs20 dispel magic. }{\fs20 The caster can leave and return to the globe without penalty.
\par Note that spell effects are not disrupted unless their effects enter the globe}{\fs20\ul ,}{\fs20  and even then they are merely suppressed, not dispelled. 
\par If a given spell has more than one level depending on which character class is casting it, use the level appropriate to the caster to determine whether }{\cs27\fs20 minor globe of invulnerability}{\fs20  stops it.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s17\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {Neutralize Poison
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\b\fs20 Conjuration (Healing)
\par }{\b\fs20 Level:}{\fs20  Acolyte 4; }{\b\fs20 Components:}{\fs20  V, S, M/DF; }{\b\fs20 Casting Time:}{\fs20  Attack action; }{\b\fs20 Range:}{\fs20  Touch; }{\b\fs20 Target:}{\fs20  Creature or object of up to 1 cu. ft./level touched; }{\b\fs20 Duration:
}{\fs20  10 minutes/level; }{\b\fs20 Saving Throw:}{\fs20  Will negates (harmless, object); }{\b\fs20 Spell Resistance:}{\fs20  Yes (harmless, object)
\par The caster detoxifies any sort of venom in the creature or object touched. A poisoned creature suffers no additional damage or effects from the poison, and any temporary effects are ended, but the spell does not reverse instantaneous effects, such as 
hit point damage, temporary ability damage, or effects that don\rquote t go away on their own.
\par The creature is immune to any poison it is exposed to during the duration of the spell. Unlike with }{\cs27\fs20 delay poison}{\fs20 , such effects aren\rquote t postponed until after the duration\emdash 
the creature is simply immune to all poison effects for the length of the spell.
