 Stone wall whose area is up to one 5-ft. square/level (S); }{\b\fs20 Duration:}{\fs20  Instantaneous; }{\b\fs20 Saving Throw:}{\fs20  See text; }{\b\fs20 Spell Resistance:}{\fs20  No
\par This spell creates a wall of rock that merges into adjoining rock surfaces.  The }{\cs27\fs20 wall of stone}{\fs20  is 1 inch thick per four caster levels and composed of up to one 5-foot square per level. You can double the wall\rquote 
s area by halving its thickness. The wall cannot be conjured so that it occupies the same space as a creature or another object.
\par A }{\cs27\fs20 wall of stone}{\fs20  can be created in al
most any shape the caster desires. The wall created need not be vertical, nor rest upon any firm foundation; however, it must merge with and be solidly supported by existing stone. If used to bridge a chasm, if the span is more than 20 feet, the wall must
 be arched and buttressed. This requirement reduces the spell\rquote s area by half. 
\par Like any other stone wall, this one can be destroyed by explosives or brought down by bludgeoning or piercing weapons. Each 5-foot square has 15 hit points per inch of thickness 
and hardness 8. A section of wall whose hit points drop to 0 is breached. If a creature tries to break through the wall with a single attack, the DC for the Strength check is 20 + 2 per inch of thickness.
\par It is possible to trap mobile opponents within or under a }{\cs27\fs20 wall of stone}{\fs20 , provided the wall is shaped so it can hold the creatures. Creatures avoid entrapment with successful Reflex saves.
